;Task:
Generate a collection filled with &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">1000</span> &nbsp; normally distributed random (or pseudo-random) numbers 
with a mean of &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">1.0</span> &nbsp; and a &nbsp; <a class="rosetta__link--wiki" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Standard_deviation" title="wp: Standard_deviation">standard deviation</a> &nbsp; of &nbsp; <span class="rosetta__text--bold">0.5</span>


Many libraries only generate uniformly distributed random numbers. 

If so, use <a class="rosetta__link--wiki" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal_distribution#Generating_values_from_normal_distribution" title="wp: Normal_distribution#Generating_values_from_normal_distribution">this formula</a> to convert them to a normal distribution.


;Related task:
* &nbsp; [[Standard deviation]]
<br><br>


=={{header|JavaScript}}==
<lang javascript>function randomNormal() {
  return Math.cos(2 * Math.PI * Math.random()) * Math.sqrt(-2 * Math.log(Math.random()))
}

var a = []
for (var i=0; i < 1000; i++){
  a[i] = randomNormal() / 2 + 1
}</lang>

